UNITED STATES of America v. DYNAMIC CHEMICAL & MINERAL CO. No. 5306. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. March 25, 1935. Dwight H. Green, of Chicago, Ill., for the United States. *1020Lloyd D. Heth and John J. Flynn, both of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and FITZ-HENRY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellees, it is now here ordered and adjudged by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
